---
description: Security and trust boundaries
globs:
  - "app/api/**"
  - "middleware.ts"
  - "auth.ts"
  - "lib/orders/**"
  - "lib/checkout/**"
  - "lib/supabase/**"
alwaysApply: false
---

Before editing APIs, auth, orders, checkout, or Supabase access, read:

- `/ai_context/03_SECURITY_RULES.md`
- `/ai_context/04_CHECKOUT_ORDERS_STRIPE.md` (if payment or order related)

Critical rules:

- Never trust client-side prices, totals, delivery fees, discounts, payment status, order status, user role, or ownership.
- `SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY` and Stripe secrets are server-only — never `NEXT_PUBLIC_*`.
- Customer order APIs require a valid `public_token`; invalid token → 404.
- Admin routes require NextAuth; verify RBAC on admin mutations.
- Stripe webhooks must verify signature and stay idempotent (`stripe_events`).

Inspect actual route handlers before changing trust boundaries.
